#. type: table
#: guix-git/doc/guix.texi:18304
msgid "As an example, an NFS file system would typically have a requirement for @code{networking}.  In some situations, requiring @code{networking} might not be sufficient as @code{networking} being marked as started does @emph{not} imply the network has already been configured and in working order (for example, when using @code{dhcpcd-client-service-type}).  For such cases, adding a requirement on a custom @code{network-online} service may be necessary.  A sample @code{network-online} one-shot Shepherd service implementation is provided below:"
